You are executing the /catchup skill for the Builds workspace.

## Purpose
Start every session with a 60-second briefing instead of spending the first few minutes
re-establishing context. Reads live state, recent logs, open decisions, and memory files
to produce a clear "here's where we are" summary.

Run this at the start of any session where you're picking up from previous work.

---

## Step 1 — Read memory files

Read the following files:
- `C:\Users\benja\.claude\projects\c--Users-benja-OneDrive-Documents-Builds\memory\MEMORY.md`
- `C:\Users\benja\.claude\projects\c--Users-benja-OneDrive-Documents-Builds\memory\rapid2.md`

Note any flagged known issues or pending items.

---

## Step 2 — Check EC2 services

For each active EC2 server, check service health and recent errors:

**Paper bot (rapid2 SSH alias):**
```bash
ssh rapid2 "sudo systemctl is-active openclaw-paper.service && \
  sudo journalctl -u openclaw-paper.service --no-pager -n 30 | grep -E 'ERROR|CRITICAL|WARNING|BUY|SELL|S3|Started|Stopped'"
```

**Production bot (3.131.96.193):**
```bash
ssh -i "C:/Users/benja/OneDrive/Documents/KeePass/AWS/rapid2-key.pem" ubuntu@3.131.96.193 \
  "sudo systemctl is-active openclaw 2>/dev/null || echo 'unreachable'"
```

---

## Step 3 — Read current portfolio state

```bash
ssh rapid2 "cat /home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/state/paper_state.json"
```

---

## Step 4 — Check for recent decisions

Look for any ADR files created recently:
```bash
ssh rapid2 "find /home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/docs/decisions -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -5"
```

Also check local:
- `Builds\Rapid2\rapid2 v1.2\docs\decisions\` (if exists)

---

## Step 5 — Check git status of active projects

```bash
cd "c:/Users/benja/OneDrive/Documents/Builds/Rapid2/rapid2 v1.2" && git log --oneline -5 && git status --short
```

---

## Step 6 — Produce the briefing

Format the output as a clean, scannable summary. Plain English throughout.

```
─── SESSION CATCHUP ─────────────────────────────────
Date: [today]

SERVICES
  Paper bot:   [active / inactive] — uptime [X]
  Live bot:    [active / inactive / unreachable]

PORTFOLIO (paper)
  Cash:        $[amount]
  Positions:   [count] open — [list symbols]
  Starting:    $[starting_value]  →  Current: $[current_total]  ([+/-X%])

RECENT ACTIVITY (last 24h)
  [any BUY/SELL entries from logs, or "no trades"]
  [any ERROR/CRITICAL lines, or "no errors"]

GIT (v1.2)
  Last commit: [message]
  Uncommitted: [files, or "clean"]

OPEN DECISIONS
  [list any recent ADR files, or "none recorded"]

KNOWN ISSUES (from memory)
  [list from rapid2.md known issues section]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Ready. What are we working on today?
```

Keep it tight — the goal is 60 seconds to read, not a full report.
If a service is down or errors are found, make those the first thing shown, not buried at the bottom.
